718257f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 72nd Street
718257f-a.text:
Central Park: The Lake, a view west towards 72nd Street, which is
shown in the background in line with the bridge.
The old Majestic Hotel is shown on the S.W. corner of Central Park
Weat and 72nd Street, and the Dakota apartment house, one of the
oldest in New York, on the N.W. corner. The building in the block
from 73rd to 74th Streets is the Langham.
1923.
L. Sperr.

718239f-b.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 72nd Street
718239f-b.text:
Central Park c The Lake, a view aoross the water towards Central
Park West and 72nd Street, showing the old Majestic Hotel in
a leafy frame.
Summer, 1923.
P. L. Sperr.
A similar view, ten years later, showing the new Majestic, a
giant apartment house, on the site of the old Majestic Hotel.
May 17, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

718469f-b.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 72nd Street
718469f-b.text:
(1)
The Dakota, one of the oldest apartment houses in New York,
Central Park West, west side, from 72nd to 73rd Streets, from
south-bound drive, Central Park at about 70th Street. At the
left may be seen a portion of the Majestic Hotel, now replaced
by the Majestic Apartment House.
October 13, 1927.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
(2)
A closer view of the Dakota.
February 2, 1929.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
